      "body" : "@gavinandresen I think your point is valid in terms of CPU mining beeing unsupported (although I love to use it on testnet to quickly generate a block), but as @sipa pointed out there is that \"issue\" in Windows, that the whole OS is lagging, when the ThreadScriptCheck is run. Also there is ThreadMessageHandler2, which uses a non-default priority on Windows... dunno why, but that is the current state ;).\n",
