      "author_association" : "NONE",
      "body" : "Current master can hit the CPU pretty hard with it's multithreading, I caught up with 50 blocks and it pegged my quad core CPU at 100%, enough to stall my GPU miner. We would expect a similar hiccup about every 10 minutes. Reindexing or downloading blocks makes it hard to watch a video or other stuff without manually lowering priority or limiting processor affinity. Bitcoin could run with default lowered priority with little impact on it's operation.\n\nWindows priority:\nhttp://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms686219%28v=vs.85%29.aspx\n",
